rComments: Really wants you to succeed, and encourages you. I love his use of the word chocolate in lectures, and he asks questions in class so that you can see if you understand. Loves to help if you don't get something However - sometimes he doesn't get your question, and will give a meh answer, but this may be due to language barriers. He gives test hints!

Great prof, really cares about your understanding of the material. Tries his best to explain the concepts and go over the example problems. Is accessible outside class through email and office hours. Tests are not exactly easy, but are fair. Mobius assignments were fair and given a good amount of time to complete. I would definitely recommend him.

He is very nice, always making sure to answer every question. The lectures are kind of boring and he goes pretty quickly, so its easy to get lost in class. The content of the exams is clear, so just practice that and you should be fine.

Best prof I had first semester at uottawa. Excellent notes, fair exams, taught well, was interactive with the class during zooms, and took time to explain concepts if people were struggling. The class was maybe half high school calc review, other half was new-ish material. Had assignments once a week which were good review of the week's content.

Dr. Fomatati is a great prof. Well put together, knowledgeable, and available to answer questions during office hours and emails. Made many concepts easier to understand. There are assignments but they are only worth 10%. Be ready to study and prepare for tests. He does prepare you well for the tests so listen up during lectures.
Run and hide. Prof is nice but this doesnt make him good at teaching. Better learn the material by yourself as in class he will only confuse you.

This prof encouraged people to participate and is always in a good mood to teach. If you don't understand something, you just have to ask him to re-explain the part you got confused about and he'll go out of his way to explain it to you. Great prof once you get used to his teaching style. Def cares about the students.
Best prof for my first semester!
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Accessible outside class', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: The way he teaches is really clear and he slowly goes through examples to make sure people will understand. When someone asks him a question, he is willing to go out of his way to explain it with different examples on a separate whiteboard.
This is by far the best professor I have ever had!
GREAT TEACHER WOULD TAKE HIS CLASS AGAIN 100%!!!!!

Ce professeur est un excellent pédagogue qui a le souci de faire réussir ses étudiants. Il a organisé un forum de discussion en ligne pour répondre aux questions, il répond toujours aux courriels, et il donne une fiche de synthèse complète aux tests. La matière est enseignée de façon claire et séquentielle.

Dr. Fomatati was an excellent prof, who seemed to genuinely want us to succeed. He created a class forum for us to interact with him and each other, he allowed multiple attempts at all exams, and he gave us the textbook PDF for free! He also let us ask questions in class, and usually answered in the forum in about an hour. Highly recommend!

On the one hand, he has a sweet and caring personality and genuinely wants his students to succeed (well-organized course notes, fair tests, easy quizzes, detailed reviews, etc.) On the other hand, his explanations during lectures are confusing at best (I had to rely a lot on external resources such as Khan Academy to fully grasp certain notions)

Was a fun class, material was pretty heavy but the prof taught it well. He cares for the students and gives them a chance to catch up if they mess up on a test. The lectures are well organized but sometimes there aren't enough examples. The prof is funny and has a great personality, would take him again!
The best math professor.

This is by far the best professor I have ever had! He cares about students and their success and is clear on what will be on tests and the final exam. He was not only a great teacher but a great person and demonstrates it throughout the course. If you have the opportunity to take him, DO IT! He is a real gem.

Amazing professor! Really cares about students and wants them to succeed. Will help you outside of class. Is very clear about what to expect on tests. He provides lots of (optional) practice questions for each lesson which really helps as it's a fast moving course. I definitely recommend this prof, he is the most caring prof you'll have.

Gives a lot of exercices after each lesson for practice. Tells you what are the chapters in a tests and gives you a lot of questions to help prepare for it. Replies to all emails. Over all good professor .
Un professeur très souriant et agréable, très pédagogique et s'assure que tout le monde a compris avant de passer d'un chapitre à un autre.
Un professeur très souriant et agréable, très pédagogique et s'assure que tout le monde a compris avant de passer d'un chapitre à un autre. A recommander !
